Jealous death snatched him from the arms of the Muses and struck him in the springtime ol his age. He now rests on the rocky banks where the Banacus rolls its murmuring waves. The Nymphs of the Adiga weep for him; for the adjacent groves heard during one night the well beloved voice of Catullus sighing melo- dious regrets on his tomb. And, at the same time, the armies of the King of F rance devastated our provinces and subjugated Liguria. The emperor, on the other hand, passed iron and fire over the territory of the Euganeans, ravaging the shores of the Sila and loading with chains the rebellious F rioul; entire Italy was plunged into mourning and desolation!
